# Commit Message Guidelines

**Primary:** `assets/docs/guides/GIT_COMMITS_GUIDE.md`  
**Extended:** `assets/docs/guides/GIT_GUIDE.md`  
**Automation:** `.gitlint` (title conventional types, lengths; body min length).  
Guide is **stricter** than gitlint where they differ (e.g. subject **50** vs gitlint title **80**).

## Format (Conventional Commits)

```gitcommit
<type>(<scope>): <description ‚Č§50 chars>

<body>

<footer>
```

### Types (use the narrow set from `GIT_COMMITS_GUIDE.md`)

`feat` `fix` `docs` `style` `ref` `test` `chore` `ci` `build`

`GIT_GUIDE.md` also lists `perf`, `revert` (and gitlint adds `perf`, `revert`, `git`) ‚ÄĒ use those when the change truly matches; default to the list above for consistency.

### Scope

Noun; area affected. Examples: `cli`, `kli`, `shell`, `config`, `biome`, `workspace`, `catalog`, `codestyle`.  
Keep scope short so the **entire subject line** stays ‚Č§**50** characters (including `type(scope): `).

## Subject line (7 rules ‚ÄĒ [cbea.ms/git-commit](https://cbea.ms/git-commit))

1. Blank line between subject and body
2. **‚Č§50 characters** total (strict; count before commit)
3. Capitalize first letter of the description; **no** trailing period
4. **Imperative mood** ‚ÄĒ ‚ÄúAdd feature‚ÄĚ, not ‚ÄúAdded‚ÄĚ / ‚ÄúAdds‚ÄĚ
5. **WHAT** in one line; details belong in the body

## Body

1. **First paragraph:** one **WHAT + WHY** sentence (intent and motivation). Not implementation steps.
2. **`Changes:`** ‚ÄĒ bullet list of **capabilities / intent**, not file-by-file or API micro-steps.
3. **`References:`** ‚ÄĒ links for specs, upstream bugs, standards (Bun, Conventional Commits, etc.) when useful.
4. Wrap body at **72** characters per line.
5. **Breaking changes:** `feat(cli)!: ‚Ä¶` and/or `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer per Conventional Commits (see `GIT_GUIDE.md`).

Do **not** add tool provenance footers (e.g. ‚ÄúMade-with: ‚Ä¶‚ÄĚ) unless the project adopts that as policy.

## Standard template (copy and fill)

```
feat(cli): Add search with FTS and filters

Enable fast full-text lookup across entry types with composable filters
for day-to-day kb navigation.

Changes:
- Search title, description, tags, and type-specific fields
- Combine FTS with --type and --tag filters
- Paginate with --page and --page-size

References:
- https://www.sqlite.org/fts5.html
```

## Checklist (before `git commit`)

- [ ] Subject ‚Č§50 characters  
- [ ] Imperative mood; capitalized; no period  
- [ ] Blank line after subject  
- [ ] Body wrapped at 72 columns  
- [ ] Summary states WHAT + WHY  
- [ ] `Changes:` bullets are intent-level  
- [ ] `References:` when external context matters  

## Atomic commits

One logical change per commit. Split mixed concerns.

